## 🔁 Spread vs Rest (Quick Difference)

| Operator           | Purpose         |
| ------------------ | --------------- |
| **Spread (`...`)** | Expands values  |
| **Rest (`...`)**   | Collects values |

### Example Together

```js
function demo(first, ...rest) {
  console.log(first); // 1
  console.log(rest);  // [2, 3]
}

demo(...[1, 2, 3]);
```

***

## ✅ Summary

✅ Spread operator works with:

*   Arrays
*   Objects
*   Function calls
*   Strings

❌ Cannot spread non-iterables like numbers:

```js
const x = ...10; // ❌ Error
```

